    "Question": {
      "content": "A negative charge is placed at point B (4.0V) between points A (8.0V) and C (-2.0V). Which way will it move?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "towards A",
        "towards B",
        "it will not move",
        "towards C"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "towards C"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Negative charges move from lower to higher potential. Point C (-2V) is lower than B (4V), so the charge moves toward C."
    },
